{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Status (rescoped 2026-06-29)\nThe spike's functional goal is MOOT. The framework already moved off forced-tool `ToolStrategy` entirely: the pydantic_ai runtime cutover means review/code/scan + the completion verifier all run on natural-termination output via `output_mode()` (`PromptedOutput`/`NativeOutput`) — there is no `ToolStrategy`/`AutoStrategy`/`ProviderStrategy` anywhere in `src/rebar`. So the BI-1 optional-None-leakage class the spike worried about is already structurally avoided, and an AutoStrategy/ProviderStrategy evaluation is no longer worth running.\n\nWhat remains is pure DOC HYGIENE: the now-stale \"disable extended thinking because forced tool-choice conflicts\" rationale still lingers in the runner/structured-output source comments and reads as if forced-tool is still in use.\n\n## Scope\n- Update/remove the stale \"disable thinking (forced tool-choice conflict)\" rationale in `src/rebar/llm/runner.py` (~lines 72-77) and `src/rebar/llm/structured.py` (~lines 11-12, 52-54) so it reflects the current pydantic_ai `PromptedOutput`/`NativeOutput` reality (keep any genuinely-still-true note as historical context, clearly labelled).\n- Record the decision in-ticket: the AutoStrategy/ProviderStrategy spike is superseded by the pydantic_ai cutover; no migration needed.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Stale forced-tool/\"disable thinking\" rationale in `runner.py` + `structured.py` is corrected or removed (no comment implies forced `ToolStrategy` is the current mechanism).\n- [ ] Decision recorded: spike moot — superseded by the pydantic_ai runtime cutover (cite that no ToolStrategy/AutoStrategy/ProviderStrategy exists in `src/rebar`).\n- [ ] `make lint` + test suite pass.","title":"Doc hygiene: correct stale forced-tool/'disable thinking' rationale (AutoStrategy spike superseded by pydantic_ai cutover)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782780874989010001,"uuid":"8ce0170c-0219-4083-a06a-c49aba7bf15b"}